snippet.textDisplay:
Your value lies not in what AI can do, but in what you can do that AI cannot.

AI is not always your ally:

👉 Weakens problem-solving and coding fundamentals.
👉Leads to errors and inefficiencies.
👉 Prevents deep learning and mastery.
👉 Misuse can damage credibility.
👉 Over-reliance may make roles replaceable.

How to Deal

✅ Support, not substitute your skills.
✅ Focus on core programming fundamentals.
✅ Verify and optimize AI-generated code.
✅ Use it to enhance knowledge, not avoid effort.
✅ Clarify your role when using AI in work.

 Balance AI use to grow skills and stay irreplaceable👌
